      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/36/1",
      "text": [
        " : \"مَنْ وَكَّلَ رَجُلاً عَلَى إِمْضَاءِ أَمْرٍ مِنَ اَلْأُمُورِ فَالْوَكَالَةُ ثَابِتَةٌ أَبَداً حَتَّى يُعْلِمَهُ بِالْخُرُوجِ مِنْهَا، كَمَا أَعْلَمَهُ بِالدُّخُولِ فِيهَا \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3381 - Jabir ibn Yazid and Mu'awiyah ibn Wahb narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) that Imam (as) said: \"Whoever appoints a man as an agent to execute a matter, the agency remains valid permanently until he informs him of its termination, just as he informed him of its initiation.\""
        ]
      }
    },
